\cf2 \cb3 This read me file helps  the reader walk through the \'93run_analysis.R\'94 script. \
\
The overall function of the \'93run_analysis.R\'94 script is to \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 {\listtext	1.	}Collect and gather data from various sources (files).\
{\listtext	2.	}Filter the data based on some given criteria.\
{\listtext	3.	}Give meaningful names to the features. As well as,  in one instance change values of an attribute to make it instantly understandable instead of requiring supplementary information.\
{\listtext	4.	}Summarize the data based on given criteria. \
{\listtext	5.	}Save the summarized tidy data.\
\pard\pardeftab720
\cf2 \
The details of the steps are as follows:\
\
1. \cf0 \cb1 The script first checks whether an unzipped directory \'93UCI HAR Dataset\'94 exists in the working directory from where the R script is being run. If not, it downloads the data and unzip it.  These steps result in the data being in downloaded in the current directory. \cf4 The data used in this project comes from this zipped source: \cf0 "https://d396qusza40orc.cloudfront.net/getdata%2Fprojectfiles%2FUCI%20HAR%20Dataset.zip"\
\
\
2. The script extracts all the relevant data from  \'93UCI HAR Dataset\'94 directory. \
	\
	The directory contains the following files and directories:\
	\
